tldr: The user requested a comprehensive aesthetic review and improvement for
  their sleep questionnaire app. The app was transformed from a generic,
  template-driven design to a calming, professional, and sleep-health-themed
  interface with a refined color palette, enhanced layouts, and polished UI
  components.
overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too
  generic. The approach began with a thorough review of the app's existing
  visual design, including global styles, main layouts, and individual UI
  components. This analysis revealed a need for a more sophisticated,
  sleep-themed color palette, improved typography, better spacing, and more
  engaging form elements. The implementation involved updating the global CSS
  with a new calming color scheme, redesigning the main questionnaire form with
  subtle background elements and a polished progress indicator, and enhancing
  the introductory section with a hero element and feature cards. Key form
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were also refined for
  better visual feedback. The report section was updated to align with the new
  theme, featuring consistent card headers and improved content presentation.
  The outcome is a visually appealing, professional, and user-friendly
  application that effectively conveys a sense of calm and trustworthiness,
  appropriate for a sleep health assessment.
